Shrimp tacos in salad form bc I couldn't find any gluten free shells. Super simple and perfect for a low carb summer meal. 
Base: pre made cole slaw mix, avo, and tomatoes.

Dressing: plain Greek yogurt, hot sauce, cumin, garlic, cilantro, red onion, jalapeno, lime - blend it up in the bullet/blender

Shrimp: cooked in a little hot sauce and chili flakes

Finish with a lot lime!!

HUMPDAY HEARTY #OATMEAL ❤️
.
I love doing these toppings build up comparison posts... it opens my eyes every time and also is helping me realise why I spent so long stuck at a plateau "eating clean foods" and not making any physical progress years ago (before I then took on macro counting without enough education🙄😂) WE LEARN from our experiences ❤️ .
1️⃣ 60g GF oats & water 
2️⃣ Add 7g raw @nuanaturals cacao powder, 10g pumpkin seeds, and chia seeds
3️⃣ Add strawberries and muesli 
4️⃣ Add @squareorganics coconut bar plus 25g Smooth PB
.
Disclaimer: I love eating lots of small meals so my square bar plus 1/3 this bowl was put into Tupperware for between this evenings classes at work 😉.
.
I agree that we should eat clean foods as much as possible that will fuel our bodies wholesomely 💗 I eat wholesome food 80/90% of the time! It is just important to be aware of your intake of such foods, depending on your goals of course 😉💗🏋. .
